Meet <b>Marcus</b> our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>Marcus has been kicking it at his quaint <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/home/?user=marcusdj"><a href='/home/?user=marcusdj'>63641-B Rosewood Road</a> manor in Ravenwood</a> for only a few weeks now. He's been a Millsberry citizen since September 18th, 2008.<br><br>In his very short time here, Marcus has been busy at work. In just a few weeks, he's managed to score trophies for Home Run Derby and Kai's Surfari.<br><br>So far he's enjoyed living in the Ravenwood neighborhood. It's quite possibly the most scenic neighborhood in Millsberry. With its old historic streets, going for a walk is always an epic adventure.<br><br>Marcus is self described as very friendly, clever, and a little smart. We think he's just being modest. <br><br>His interests include baseball, basketball, and other games. Basketball and baseball occupy his winters, springs, and summers, but what about fall? Marcus likes to reserve fall for those nice autumn strolls in Peabody Park.<br><br>If you're going to buy Marcus a present, it shouldn't be too hard figuring out what to get him. When it comes to music, Marcus enjoys rap, rap, and more rap. There's nothing wrong with knowing what you like.<br><br>If you happen to bump into Marcus, be sure to pat him on the back and congratulate him for being such an outstanding citizen!<br></div>
